As >>22534879 points out, there are many different kinds of intersexuality. And they have very different physical symptoms.
Texanon claims to not know what kind of intersexuality he has. This is legitimately preposterous.
We know that Tex has intersex genitalia, meaning that he has a 'severe' (for lack of a better word) form of intersexuality. This contrasts with some chromosomal forms of intersexuality which have little to no effect on a person's body, and can go undiscovered for life. Doctors would have noticed Tex's genitalia while he was in the womb. With Tex's parents' permission, doctors would have been able to determine exactly what kind of intersexuality Tex had - if not before birth, then soon after. It is highly likely that Tex's parents would have given permission for these tests because it is medically important information. Different kinds of intersexuality have a profound effect on the body's interaction with certain medications, risks of medical conditions, cancers, etc. It is vital for a parent to know these things.
But okay. Maybe Tex's parents didn't get these tests done, or they did, but they never told Tex the results, leaving him unsure. It doesn't matter, because Tex has been hospitalised multiple times in his life, including as an independent adult. If Texanon couldn't tell the doctors what kind of intersexuality he has, they would have tested him immediately upon entry and told him the results. Again, this is vital medical information, like doing a blood test, there's no way to get around it.

Against all appearances Nietzsche is actually an extraordinarily difficult thinker, who must be read comprehensively and with a great deal of clarity to begin to properly understand. These are the three great Nietzsche interpretations of the 20th century.

Just balanced. I avoid sugar and try to avoid refined carbs where I can. Don't have meat with every meal. Lots of fruit and veggies and maybe one meal with meat per day. the effect my preset has:
- fixes the mono-y mp3 sound of winamp with mathematicaly linear stereo widening
- adds sound up to 20khz through harmonic extrapolation
- improves impulse sounds and constant sounds through a selective amp algorythm
- adds missing bass through a harmonic extrapolation frequency filler
- reduces vaolume and uses a bass frequency clipper to prevent digital clipping (this, combined with the other effects, creates improved dynamics)

the cpu is set up in a way to produce non-degraded sound (which often happens with dsps) in multicore systems.

slowly. u aren’t gonna be going from a whole new closet overnight, it takes time. focus on basics first - simple clothes in the style u like that u can wear out. for dark academia, stuff like button downs or more formal slacks/skirts would be good. then, as you continue to build out your basics, start to get statement pieces or more expensive stuff (a nice coat, a bag you like, a nice sweater) etc. matching basics with big pieces and learning your colors is the way to go

It’s an app that lets you look at stuff and rate yes or no. Then you get a box every month and it has a custom set of 5 things picked by a stylist for you based on some info you give them. Then you rate the stuff, re-hire or fire the stylist you had the previous month, and get another box the next month. They also show you collections of items that pair well with stuff you have so you can get more if you want (you can always buy what you want directly from them too.)

>OSR is only good for nostalgia. 5e is perfectly fine for everything but rolling for stats.
I disagree. B/X is a much more elegant game than 5e. Combat is over in 1-3 rounds and doesn't have inflated HP totals. The XP system rewards treasure hunting over combat, which synchronizes with the core dungeon crawling gameplay loop instead of wandering through a line of railroaded DM plot points. The game only has 4 human classes and 3 nonhuman races, which is all you need for classic fantasy - a city full of mushroom people isn't so mystical in 5e when you have warforged astral self monks and psionic tiefing knights at home. That, and you don't have to make charisma rolls for intimidation or persuasion which means you won't be foiled by the d20 after actually doing good roleplaying.

5e doesn't use 3d6 down the line because you need to roll skill checks for absolutely everything. Player skill is much more important in OSR.
>but it makes for a different D&D game one which modern rules and modern players just aren't built for.
I mean, it definitely makes for a different game. 5e has almost no mechanics for exploration at all, and the ones that exist are almost unplayable RAW. Personally I find dungeon crawling much more engaging when light isn't just an unlimited cantrip and your torch is a fragile safeguard between the party and a darkness full of monsters, but that's me, and I'm not exactly an old gamer who was around when this stuff was current.

>>28750375
nta but a few things,
1. Offering state-assisted suicide to people with depression creates a negative incentive for there to be some sort of "end" to studying therapeutic treatment of mental illnesses. Treatment of mental illness is complicated, but I, like most people probably, do not think that suicide is the answer for most of them. Treatment for mental illness often kind of sucks, but people are learning and trying to improve the practice constantly, ranging from new therapy approaches to new medicine to finding out old medicines might not work as well as we thought. I feel like state-sanctioned suicide would reduce growth in these areas.

2. I personally struggled with depression for instance for much of my teenage and early adult life, but I do not feel that way any longer. I think that were it just an option to die, I and many other people would have likely died before having a chance to experience better things in life.

3. I think what governments choose to support is not just something to consider from a perspective of legality but from what the goals of the society it represents are. It seems like nothing this represents is really a good thing. It feels like this is the government saying it has given up on improving the conditions of its people or that the medical and academic institutions it has funded will just not find a way to meaningfully help.

4. I think it enables a bad mindset for the mentally unwell and will also lead to people dying who are not unwell enough that they cannot recover. I remember some old forum that described "living with suicide" that I strongly related to where people would constantly fantasize about esoteric or detailed plans to commit suicide. I believe that, with legal assisted suicide, people would instead plan for that, and in many cases if gatekeeping is lax enough, go through with it when they are not really that sick.

>>28709276

Conjugated Estrogens: (Moderate) Modafinil is an inducer of CYP3A hepatic enzymes. Estrogens are metabolized by CYP3A4. A decrease in estrogen concentrations, and thus efficacy, may occur in patients taking estrogens for hormone replacement therapy. If these drugs are used together, monitor patients for a decrease in clinical effects. Dosage adjustments may be necessary.

Basically modafinil/armodafinil increases inactivation of hormonal contraception (both estrogen and progestins) by 30-50%.

i mean it's technically SSI. i'm partially physically disabled now, which means renewal is easy every few years, but when i got it it was mostly just c-ptsd & various things stemming from or related to that. i experienced serial sexual and emotional abuse as a child and suffer from pretty severe panic attacks and spikes of social anxiety.

applying for SSI is just filling out a bunch of paperwork and basically telling the government that you are godforsaken scum. it's pretty humiliating and i wound up crying so much while applying i had to have other people help me fill it out. it's extremely commonly denied, but you can apply again some months after a denial. once you are approved, you'll receive backpay from the date you applied.

once you're about a year out from the application if you failed, a law firm will take your case for a % of the back payment (and you only pay if you win) and usually tell you to see someone who will write a paper with your application promising that you are human refuse. certain states are way worse than others to get approved in (i had one of the hardest lol), but you often need to do this anywhere. like most government approval, outside help winds up being an almost necessary part of the process because our economy is entirely built on inefficiency and insurance and we'd collapse without money traps.

you'll usually need to not be working for the entire period to get approved, so if you're homeless or on the verge of it they're usually kind of hoping you just die. you also cannot save money once you're on it. when my partner moved in we were barely surviving off just my SSI for like a year

>>28740647
life is actually pretty great, these days (minus my body kind-of falling apart and occasional trauma flare-ups), don't worry about me. this is quite a few years behind me and was just extraordinarily miserable at the time. i understand most people apply in somewhat similar conditions and a lot of times the biggest thing to getting it is a little help or a good push to apply.

i really suggest anyone considering getting on it to not wait and just send out an application ASAP. you basically *want* to get denied once and get that over with (don't get your hopes up that you'll get it on the first go) and build that year up. first-time applications are extremely frequently denied and you can spend the year researching how you want to improve the second application.

i've had several friends throughout the years who had to get on it and it went pretty similarly for each of them. it really helps if you have a helpful relative or someone you're getting free rent off of - you fill out on the paperwork that you're paying (even if you aren't - your friend/family just need to say you are) to generate backpayment. sometimes people working at the government offices are really understanding of how fucking bullshit the terms are and will help you outright lie to get on this shit or receive higher payment lol - but don't count on it. emphasize at every opportunity how much what is going on interferes with your ability to work and how it's a consistent impossibility. you nearly need to imply you can barely dress yourself without a breakdown.

absolutely do not give into (or allow friends to give into) "ah god i'm human scum i'm a burden to society i should kms i don't deserve help" - this care is extremely goddamn basic humanitarian aid with ludicrously inhumane conditions to get on. fuck the system to hell, fuck the concept of "earning" or "deserving" it to hell, it's a means to survive.

good luck
